<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 27 at 5:15PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern Anson
and south central Richmond Counties through 615 PM EDT...
At 515 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles west of Rockingham, moving southwest at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Rockingham, Wadesboro, Lilesville, Morven, McFarlan, Diggs and
Blewett Falls Lake.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
